Venezuela must compete for oil investment - Conoco . Venezuela will be the third most important region for U . S . oil giant Conoco after North America and Western Europe by 2003 , the company ' s chief executive said on Wednesday . But south - east Asia is hot on its heels in the race to attract invesments and Venezuela must continue reforms to stay competitive , Archie Dunham told journalists . He was impressed with the progress made by Venezuela president Rafael Caldera , but said investors wanted more change in three key areas : VAT tax refunds , dollar tax accounting and labour laws . 
